"Abstract When a website is designed, it may include a number of key words in its code which reflect the content of the website. These are known as metatags and they enable a company’s site to be catalogued according to such matters as the title of the web page, the company’s name, its trademarks, history, type of business and location. Metatags are used in particular by certain search engines to match key search words against the metatags available — inevitably the validity of the search will very much depend on the original use of the metatags on a website."
